Package: lochs
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: socat
Description: FreeBSD jail management for Linux
 Lochs is a Docker-like container management CLI for running FreeBSD
 jails on Linux. It includes the bsdulator engine for ptrace-based
 FreeBSD syscall translation.
 .
 Features include:
  - Run FreeBSD binaries natively on Linux
  - Jail creation, networking, and volume management
  - Image pull/push with OCI-compatible registries
  - Web dashboard with REST API on port 8420
  - Compose files for multi-container orchestration
  - ZFS snapshot integration
  - Cgroup v2 resource limits and health checks
